CoreGx method for Signature Search

tcm.SSwithCoreGx.Rd

CoreGx method for Signature Search

tcm.SSwithCoreGx(input, data, cores = 1L)

Arguments

input

A data.frame containing logFC value, which rownames should be gene symbols.
data

A data.frame contains logFC value data from 103 compounds.
cores

Number of cores to run the task

Value

A data.frame.

Examples

data("data_logFC")
query2 <- data_logFC[1:60, 1, drop = FALSE]
txp <- tcm.SSwithCoreGx(query2, data_logFC[1:3])

#> 60 / 12548 genes in input share identifiers with reference database
#> Registered S3 method overwritten by 'sets':

#>   print.element ggplot2
